// What will the following code log to the console and why? Don't run it until 
// you have tried to answer.

let myWords = ['Hello'];
myWords.push('Goodbye');

console.log(myWords);

// Solution: Will output `['Hello', 'Goodbye']`.

// On line 4 global variable is declared and initialised with value `['Hello']`.

// On line 5 `myWords` calls the array method `push` which appends the argument
// passed to it, `'Goodbye'` to the end of `myWords` and returns the new length
// `2`.

// `push` mutates the array that `myWords` points to so that it is now `['Hello', 'Goodbye']`.

// Hence on line 7 when `console.log` is invoked with the argument passed to
// it the value of `myWords` it outputs `['Hello', 'Goodbye']`.